## Risk & Compliance

| Change | Business Risk | Regulatory Angle | Act By |
|--------|--------------|-----------------|--------|
| **[Exchange Server CVE-2026-42897 — OWA JavaScript injection](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/addressing-exchange-server-may-2026-vulnerability-cve-2026-42897/ba-p/4518498)** | An attacker can execute malicious code in a user's browser by sending a crafted email opened in Outlook Web Access. Affects Exchange 2016, 2019, and SE running on-premises. | HIPAA Security Rule; CMMC AC/SI controls; cyber insurance breach notification triggers | Now — June 2026 SU is available |
| **[EWS API retirement in Exchange Online — October 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/introducing-ewsallowedappids-preparing-for-the-final-phase-of/ba-p/4529471)** | Line-of-business applications, third-party tools, and custom integrations using EWS will stop working when Microsoft disables the API. Revenue or operations loss if applications go dark. | SOC 2 availability controls; HIPAA electronic transactions if clinical systems are affected | October 2026 — inventory and migrate now |
| **[Exchange ActiveSync certificate-based authentication retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/retirement-of-direct-exchange-activesync-certificate-based/ba-p/4517896)** | Mobile email clients using direct certificate authentication to Exchange Online will lose access before end of 2026. New tenants are already blocked. | NIST CSF Identity Management; CMMC IA controls | End of 2026 — begin migration immediately |
| **[Entra ID legacy MFA and Conditional Access control retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-what-organizations-need-to/ba-p/4522024)** | Custom MFA controls, unregistered SSPR methods, and inconsistent Conditional Access enforcement are being retired. Gaps in authentication policy could open phishing exposure. | NIST CSF PR.AC; cyber insurance MFA requirements; HIPAA access controls | Begin migration planning now |
| **[AI agents accessing enterprise data — governance gap](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/securing-ai-agents-end-to-end-connecting-purview-dspm-agent-365/ba-p/4521155)** | Copilot Cowork, Microsoft Scout, computer-using agents, and third-party model integrations are now GA. Without data security posture controls in Purview, sensitive data may be surfaced or exfiltrated by AI workflows with no audit trail. | GDPR data minimization; HIPAA minimum necessary standard; SOC 2 logical access | Within 30 days — review Purview DSPM posture |
| **[EWS legacy TLS deprecation for POP and IMAP](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/deprecating-legacy-tls-and-endpoints-for-pop-and-imap-in/ba-p/4515201)** | Older email clients and scripts connecting via TLS 1.0 or 1.1 for POP3/IMAP4 will lose connectivity when Microsoft completes the deprecation. | NIST CSF PR.DS encryption standards; PCI DSS TLS requirements | Plan within 60 days |

