## What Your Employees Will Notice

- **SharePoint looks different.** A visual refresh is rolling out with cleaner layouts and updated navigation. Content and links remain in place; this is a cosmetic change but will prompt questions.
- **Copilot is smarter with images.** Copilot Chat can now read charts, diagrams, and screenshots embedded in Word, PowerPoint, and PDF files when generating answers.
- **Copilot Cowork is generally available.** Employees with Microsoft 365 Copilot licenses can now delegate multi-step tasks to an agentic system inside the redesigned Copilot app. This is the platform's most significant productivity capability launch this year and will drive both enthusiasm and support questions.
- **Microsoft Scout has launched.** This always-on personal agent is integrated across Microsoft 365 apps. Users will begin seeing it in their daily workflows without explicit opt-in in some configurations.
- **Teams voice enrollment is arriving.** Users will be prompted to register their voice profile in Teams settings. This enables speaker recognition in meeting transcripts. Admins can disable this feature if it conflicts with policy.
- **Copilot calls and answers your Teams Phone.** Employees who enable call delegation can have Copilot screen and respond to incoming calls on their behalf. Communication to users about expectations around this feature is advisable before it surprises callers.
- **Wi-Fi workplace check-in in Teams.** Employees who opt in will have their office location updated automatically when connected to configured company networks. This is opt-in and tied to privacy settings.
- **Copilot Notebooks is available to more users.** Previously limited to Copilot licensees, Notebooks is now rolling out to Copilot Chat users, giving more employees a shared AI-powered workspace.
- **Learning Agent is generally available.** Personalized AI skill recommendations now appear inside Teams, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint for Copilot users.

*Sources: [SharePoint Blog — Visual Refresh](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-sharepoint-blog/a-new-sharepoint-look-and-feel-what-s-changing-and-why-it/ba-p/4529776) · [Microsoft 365 Copilot Blog — May 2026 What's New](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/what-s-new-in-microsoft-365-copilot-may-2026/ba-p/4522010) · [Microsoft 365 Blog — Copilot Cowork GA](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/blog/2026/06/16/copilot-cowork-is-now-generally-available/)*

---

## What Your Help Desk Should Expect

- **SharePoint visual refresh confusion.** Users will report that SharePoint "looks broken" or that navigation has moved. Prepare a one-paragraph communication explaining the intentional redesign.
- **Copilot Cowork and Scout setup questions.** Employees who see these new experiences will ask how to use them, whether they are included in their license, and how to give Copilot access to the right content. Volume will be high in the first two weeks.
- **Teams voice enrollment prompts.** Users will ask whether they must enroll their voice and what data is stored. Have a ready answer on your organization's policy before the prompt appears.
- **Mobile email access failures.** Organizations with any users authenticating via Exchange ActiveSync using client certificates should expect escalations as new-tenant blocks propagate and as broader enforcement approaches.
- **Legacy application connectivity alerts.** IT teams inventorying EWS-dependent applications may surface tickets from business units whose tools are flagged for upcoming disconnection. The new EWSAllowedAppIDs allowlist tool will generate questions about which apps to add.
- **"My Copilot answered my phone" calls.** Users who discover Copilot call delegation unintentionally may file complaints or confusion tickets. Consider a proactive communication before this feature is widely noticed.
- **Intune capability questions from IT admins.** With advanced Intune features arriving in E3/E5 tenants by August 1, IT administrators will begin asking about new management tools and workflows. Budget time for internal training.

*Sources: [Exchange Team Blog — EWS Retirement](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/introducing-ewsallowedappids-preparing-for-the-final-phase-of/ba-p/4529471) · [Teams Blog — Copilot Call Delegation](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-teams-blog/focus-on-the-teams-phone-calls-that-matter-most-with-copilot/ba-p/4512533) · [Intune Blog — E3/E5 Packaging](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/it-experts-weigh-in-advanced-intune-capabilities-coming-to/ba-p/4516898)*

