## Cost & Licensing

**Advanced Intune capabilities included in E3/E5 at no additional cost — effective July 1.** Capabilities previously requiring the Intune Suite add-on are being bundled into Microsoft 365 E3 and E5. Eligible customers will see them in their tenants by August 1. If your organization purchased the Intune Suite as a standalone add-on, work with your Microsoft account team to review whether that add-on remains necessary.

**New Microsoft 365 Business with Copilot SKUs launch July 1.** Microsoft is introducing new small-business SKUs with Copilot built in. Organizations in the SMB segment or those managing subsidiaries on Business tiers should review licensing with their reseller before July 1 to understand how existing seats map to the new structure.

**Purview Data Lifecycle Management billing model change incoming.** A new billing model for DLM will charge based on the volume of data retained, priced at $0.25 per GB per month for non-Microsoft 365 generative AI prompts and responses. Organizations retaining large volumes of Copilot or third-party AI interaction data should model the cost impact before the change takes effect.

**Exchange 2016/2019 Period 2 ESU is a cost item.** If your organization did not complete migration to Exchange Subscription Edition by April 2026, you are in the fee-based Period 2 ESU program running through October 2026. Budget accordingly and accelerate migration planning to exit this spend.

*Sources: [Intune Blog — E3/E5 Packaging](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/it-experts-weigh-in-advanced-intune-capabilities-coming-to/ba-p/4516898) · [Microsoft 365 Blog — Business with Copilot SKUs](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/blog/2026/05/28/introducing-microsoft-365-business-with-copilot-the-new-standard-for-small-business/) · [M365 Roadmap — DLM Billing Change](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=560324)*

